&lt;LI&gt;All for one and one for all - AE War Cries are still a big item on our wish list. If you don’t want powerful group disciplines to be AE’d then please create a special AE line for raids that is tuned appropriately. If you fear that AE War Cries would lessen the desire for multiple Berserkers on a raid, make the AE line shorter duration or add offensive/defensive War Cries (see above).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;We didn't recieve a new Warcry since Gates of Discord.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B&gt;5. Throwing - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Some improvements are being considered as part of round #1 of the class Re-Envision process.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Throwing has a few problems that need to be addressed:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;The lack of good throwing weapons and the disadvantage of throwing weapons vs. a bow (see above).&lt;BR&gt;It would be absolutely great if the throwing skill could be reworked to work more closely to how Archery works. A bow like item in the range slot, i.e. a throwing glove or throwing satchel, that isn’t thrown away but rather enhances the range, damage and delay of the ammo (the actual axes, shurikens, knives, stones, etc). These bow-equivalents could be seeded across existing group, raid and crafting content and could be shared with Monks, Rogues, Beastlords, etc.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;The cost of summoned axes / lack of an endless quiver type AA make our throwing a heavy burden on our purses. It’s especially a bummer for those of us that wish to kite as a form of soloing. Please do the right thing and remove the cost for the components and/or give us an Endless Quiver AA. It’s a really inappropriate money sink, which also scares off new players from trying this class.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Another problem with the current throwing weapons is the range of our throwing axes. The best one is currently 175 which is not enough to 'dodge' from AEs in raid encounters. Therefore, throwing isn't even a viable alternative to melee combat in those situations. Please extend it beyond 200 - any lvl 55+ bow has a range of 175 and can be easily extended beyond 200 with cheap arrows (even mage summoned arrows)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B&gt;6. Combat Abilities - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Our Jolt line is on the same timer as our ‘offensive’ / agro-creating skills. The problem with this is that we very rarely grab agro from melee damage alone. In normal circumstances it only happens right after we used a stun, snare or volley attack and then our Jolt line is unavailable for 12 seconds.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Snares: This ability line scales very poorly as the only difference from upgrading is the resist adjust field, which does not seem to make that much of a difference. The price for that upgrade is a great increase in endurance cost as well as monetary component cost (see #6 Throwing). We would appreciate if the duration and the Snare percentage would scale up with each rank as well. Right now they are all 55% snare with a 1 minute duration. I would suggest a 35%, 1minute, 45%, 2minute, 55% 3minute, 65% 4minute progression.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Stuns: There is a gap in the stun progression in the mid 50s. The level 40 stun skill can stun NPCs up to level 55 while the next upgrade to the Stun line is available at level 60. Most NPCs in the lower planes where a typical mid 50s player would hunt are above level 55 and therefore immune to this stun.&lt;BR&gt;Another smaller gap appears between in the 65ish – 68 range as the level 60 stun works on NPCs up to level 65 and the next stun upgrade occurs at level 68; although this gap isn’t as dramatic as the previous one as most exp spots for that level range feature numerous NPCs of level 65 or below.&lt;BR&gt;I don’t really have an easy solution for this problem other than reviewing all the stun and adding more ranks to make the progression smoother, always allowing the Berserker to stun NPCs at least a few levels above him.&lt;BR&gt;For the high ends this problem returns again as the highest level stun works on NPCs up to level 70, which isn’t sufficient to work in places like Riftseekers or the Nest, therefore many have asked for a new stun or a stun AA that raises the level up to 72/73ish&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B&gt;7. Endurance Regeneration - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;The innate endurance regeneration rate does not improve between level 65 and 70, while all combat abilities have become more expensive.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;We would very much like to see endurance regeneration items and/or spells to be added to the game.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;The slow rate of endurance regeneration becomes especially noticeable after resurrections or raid ‘burn’ situations. In the high end it can take 20 minutes or longer of pure idle time to recover from 0 endurance to full. Some ‘resting’ skill that allows us to regenerate endurance faster but adds some negatives to avoid abuse, i.e. all disc / combat ability timers greyed out for a 5 – 10 minutes or limited movement and attack speed while ‘resting’, would be appreciated.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
