    <item>
      <title>Re: Class issues lists – Updated Version (Berserker)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=berserkerbalance&amp;message.id=2927#M2927</link>
      <description>&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **Zowie**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff00ff&gt;Berserker - List Update scheduled for&amp;nbsp;11/19/04&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;OL&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Overall Melee performance &lt;SPAN&gt;–&lt;FONT color=#9933ff&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This is a new item that was added with the 11/05 update, we currently do not have any development feedback on this issue.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Berserkers aren't really happy with their general melee performance yet and feel that we need something to push us ahead of the baseline warriors to make us a true dps class. Here are some ideas for improvements:&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Our piercing cap should be equal to our 2hb and 2hs cap. (252 at lvl 65 and 270 at lvl 70 - Currently it is 240 at lvl 65 and 260 at lvl 70)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Give us a special damage table like monks or innate bonuses like damage modifiers&amp;nbsp;(analog to Warriors mitigation bonus), higher innate crit rates than other classes, etc.&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Add Specialize 2handed slash , blunt and piercing: a skill that gives a small delay reduction like the 100 hands effect before ordinary haste applies and increases accuracy. As with the caster specialization you can only choose one weapontype to master.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;An innate bane to our weapons by type, i.e. 2hb +3 undead 2hs +3 humanoid 2hp +2 whatever&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;2H weapons generally have lower stats than equal level 1h-1h or 1h-shield combos. Other classes can choose which combination they want to use in order optimize their performance accordingly to the situation but Berserkers are stuck with 2h Weapons no matter what. Either increase the overall stats on 2H weapons or give Berserkers a bonus on 2H weapons (A code similar to the Recommended Level code could be used that would grant Berserkers additional 25 - 50% of the weapon stats. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Frenzy &lt;SPAN&gt;–&lt;FONT color=#9933ff&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated - Reworded version&amp;nbsp; was added with the 11/05 update, we currently do not have any new development feedback on this issue.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We would like to see a higher minimum damage value added for Frenzy (pre-AAs). Currently we can Frenzy for 3 points of damage. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The scaleability of this scale is very poor. It skill caps out very early at 200 and it is completely weapon independent. So between the time where a Berserker maxes out the skill (around lvl 40) and gets his Frenzy improvement AAs (usually around lvl 65 or even later). The skill is stagnant is pretty much stagnant.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Reevaluate the Endurance Cost of our Abilities.&amp;nbsp;– &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This is a new item that was added with the 11/05 update, we currently do not have any development feedback on this issue.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The cost of some of the abilities (especially the 3rd rank and above) as well as all Warcries seem to be a bit over the top. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Itemization -&lt;FONT color=#9933ff&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This is still in progress&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;BER only Weapons - Add some BER only weapons similar to other classes. From Ssra to elemental pet weapon to Time level.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;There is simply not enough class specific armor or weapons for the berserker as he progresses through the previous content.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Create a style of Berserker only type of weapons, perhaps extremely heavy weapons, or specialized throwing weapons.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Warcry Improvements –&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The effectiveness of Warcries is still nothing that makes people really *want* Berserkers. It has too little effect on the damage output of the group.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Add a MGB skill for Warcry or a new tomes that are MGB'able. (See Raid utitility) - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;There are no plans for a MGB ability for berserkers.&amp;nbsp; Warcry is meant to be single group only.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Recast time is too long for the impact of the effect.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Increase the range of Warcry. Especially in raid situations the groupmembers may spread out further than the current 60 range and will therefore miss the effect.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Add a "purify" attribute to Warcries that remove detrimental effects on the group/raid or turn them off for the duration of the Warcry. The idea is that the Warcry puts our friends in such an agitated state that they ignore the pain and don't fear death. This would increase desireability in groups/raids and would also add something that casters can benefit from.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;There is no new Warcry 66+&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Throwing - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated - This item had additions added to it with the 11/05 update, we currently do not have any new development feedback on this issue.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Throwing is currently the weakest form of damage for berserkers… its currently bugged as well.&amp;nbsp; From my understanding the proc rate on the Tainted Axe of hatred is supposed to be very high… sadly it isn’t.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Increase the BASE damage of Throwing&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Add a Quiver type of ammo slot bag..&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Remove component cost. It seems like the Dev crew has realized that taxing a class for using their basic abilities with money sinks is 'a bad thing(tm)'. (See removal of cleric's peridot cost from Symbol/Aego line). I don't think that we should suffer from these reagent costs as there is virtually no other source of readily available throwing items for us available.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We would like to see an Endless Quiver AA. Carrying around components and stacks of axes is very tedious, especially when you need to summon tons of axes for a raid fight.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Remove the casting time on axe summons. If we run out of axes mid-fight and need to summon new Axes we have to pause for 2 seconds on every summon. This lowers our DPS considereably. For comparison, a Ranger (without Endless Quiver) that carries his Fletching Kit and components around only has to click the combine button which doesn't take any time to cast or interrupts his combat.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Don't forget to consider throwing on the upcoming archery-autofire function. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;This is currently how Auto-Fire works&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The way that throwing currently works we can't have a stat item in Range slot and still be able to use throwing (unless the stat item of course is a throwing axe). With Archery, this problem is solved through bows which have decent stats. Allow us to throw items from ammo slot and kep a stat item range slot or add bow equivalent items for throwing (throwing gloves, magical sharpening stones, etc.)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Reconsider the range of throwing weapons. The best one is currently 175 which is not enough to 'dodge' from AEs in raid encounters. Therefore, throwing isn't even a viable alternative to meleeing in those situations. Please extend it beyond 200 - any lvl 55+ bow has a range of 175 and can be easily extended beyond 200 with cheap arrows (even mage summoned arrows)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Abilities - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This item had additions added to it with the 11/05 update, we currently do not have any new development feedback on this issue.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The level 67 snare is random duration. All other snares are fixed duration.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Frenzy and Kick are on same timers, separate them.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We need a Stun and SNARE on different timers.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Stun Endurance cost needs to be lowered&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Snare should scale with each new rank (level 8 snare is as good at the level 65 one)&amp;nbsp; I suggest 1 minute, 2 minute, 3 minute set times on each.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Jolt needs its own timer as well…&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Endurance Regen -&lt;FONT color=#9933ff&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated, Reworded version&amp;nbsp; was added with the 11/05 update, we currently do not have any new development feedback on this issue.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Innate Endurance regen doesn't improve from 65 to 70 while all abilities become more costly in endurance cost.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Berserkers suffer the most from endurance use, so there must be a way for us to get better endurance return… I suggest Flowing Thought for endurance&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;No Raid Utility - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated, Reworded version&amp;nbsp; was added with the 11/05 update, we currently do not have any new development feedback on this issue.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We need something besides medicore dps to help our group/raid.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Ideas tossed around are more combat abilities, innate group bonuses, AE Warcrys, and AE abilities that improve the raid. (Maybe + Accuracy or + Strikethrough).&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We should be able to provide such skills most of the time, NOT like current Warcry only once every 30 minutes.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We need something class defining that gives us an attractive niche to fill.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improved DPS -&amp;nbsp;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt; - &lt;FONT size=2&gt;DPS for all classes to be&amp;nbsp;re-evaluated in the future&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;I have done much research into the damage comparisons of Rogues, Warriors, Monks, and Berserkers; I have found that Rogues do the most DPS by a large margin… Berserkers do about 60% of what a rogue can do.&amp;nbsp; That means that 1 rogue is worth 2 berserkers, since we have no other utility to offer outside of our DPS.&amp;nbsp; My suggestion is to somehow improve our DPS to at least 80% of a rogue&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;By limiting berserkers to 2handed weapons only, you have extremely limited our paths of progression.&amp;nbsp; The quality of 2handers coming out of GoD is also very bad…. They are either too fast, or have no AC.&amp;nbsp; You introduced a lot of 2handers with dumb procs like Guard 3… WHY!?&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;/OL&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Ashlanne on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;11-19-2004&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;01:21 PM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Fri, 19 Nov 2004 21:19:32 GMT</pubDate>
      <author>Ashlanne</author>
      <guid>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=berserkerbalance&amp;message.id=2927#M2927</guid>
      <dc:creator>Ashlanne</dc:creator>
      <dc:date>2004-11-19T21:19:32Z</dc:date>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Re: Class issues lists – Updated Version (Berserker)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=berserkerbalance&amp;message.id=2913#M2913</link>
      <description>&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt?&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff00ff&gt;Berserker - List Update scheduled for&amp;nbsp;11/05/04&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;OL&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Overall Melee performance &lt;SPAN&gt;–&lt;FONT color=#9933ff&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(NEW)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Berserkers aren't really happy with their general melee performance yet and feel that we need something to push us ahead of the baseline warriors to make us a true dps class. Here are some ideas for improvements: &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Our piercing cap should be equal to our 2hb and 2hs cap. (252 at lvl 65 and 270 at lvl 70 - Currently it is 240 at lvl 65 and 260 at lvl 70)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Give us a special damage table like monks or innate bonuses like damage modifiers&amp;nbsp;(analog to Warriors mitigation bonus), higher innate crit rates than other classes, etc. &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Add Specialize 2handed slash , blunt and piercing: a skill that gives a small delay reduction like the 100 hands effect before ordinary haste applies and increases accuracy. As with the caster specialization you can only choose one weapontype to master.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;An innate bane to our weapons by type, i.e. 2hb +3 undead 2hs +3 humanoid 2hp +2 whatever&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;2H weapons generally have lower stats than equal level 1h-1h or 1h-shield combos. Other classes can choose which combination they want to use in order optimize their performance accordingly to the situation but Berserkers are stuck with 2h Weapons no matter what. Either increase the overall stats on 2H weapons or give Berserkers a bonus on 2H weapons (A code similar to the Recommended Level code could be used that would grant Berserkers additional 25 - 50% of the weapon stats. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Frenzy &lt;SPAN&gt;–&lt;FONT color=#9933ff&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated - reworded version passed along&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We would like to see a higher minimum damage value added for Frenzy (pre-AAs). Currently we can Frenzy for 3 points of damage. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The scaleability of this scale is very poor. It skill caps out very early at 200 and it is completely weapon independent. So between the time where a Berserker maxes out the skill (around lvl 40) and gets his Frenzy improvement AAs (usually around lvl 65 or even later). The skill is stagnant is pretty much stagnant.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Reevaluate the Endurance Cost of our Abilities.&amp;nbsp;– &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(NEW)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The cost of some of the abilities (especially the 3rd rank and above) as well as all Warcries seem to be a bit over the top. &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Itemization -&lt;FONT color=#9933ff&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This is still in progress&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;BER only Weapons - Add some BER only weapons similar to other classes. From Ssra to elemental pet weapon to Time level.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;There is simply not enough class specific armor or weapons for the berserker as he progresses through the previous content.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Create a style of Berserker only type of weapons, perhaps extremely heavy weapons, or specialized throwing weapons.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Warcry Improvements –&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(NEW)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The effectiveness of Warcries is still nothing that makes people really *want* Berserkers. It has too little effect on the damage output of the group.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Add a MGB skill for Warcry or a new tomes that are MGB'able. (See Raid utitility)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Recast time is too long for the impact of the effect.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Increase the range of Warcry. Especially in raid situations the groupmembers may spread out further than the current 60 range and will therefore miss the effect.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Add a "purify" attribute to Warcries that remove detrimental effects on the group/raid or turn them off for the duration of the Warcry. The idea is that the Warcry puts our friends in such an agitated state that they ignore the pain and don't fear death. This would increase desireability in groups/raids and would also add something that casters can benefit from.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;There is no new Warcry 66+&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Throwing - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated additions to this item have been passed along&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Throwing is currently the weakest form of damage for berserkers… its currently bugged as well.&amp;nbsp; From my understanding the proc rate on the Tainted Axe of hatred is supposed to be very high… sadly it isn’t.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Increase the BASE damage of Throwing&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Add a Quiver type of ammo slot bag..&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Remove component cost. It seems like the Dev crew has realized that taxing a class for using their basic abilities with money sinks is 'a bad thing(tm)'. (See removal of cleric's peridot cost from Symbol/Aego line). I don't think that we should suffer from these reagent costs as there is virtually no other source of readily available throwing items for us available.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We would like to see an Endless Quiver AA. Carrying around components and stacks of axes is very tedious, especially when you need to summon tons of axes for a raid fight.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Remove the casting time on axe summons. If we run out of axes mid-fight and need to summon new Axes we have to pause for 2 seconds on every summon. This lowers our DPS considereably. For comparison, a Ranger (without Endless Quiver) that carries his Fletching Kit and components around only has to click the combine button which doesn't take any time to cast or interrupts his combat.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Don't forget to consider throwing on the upcoming archery-autofire function. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;This is currently how Auto-Fire works&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The way that throwing currently works we can't have a stat item in Range slot and still be able to use throwing (unless the stat item of course is a throwing axe). With Archery, this problem is solved through bows which have decent stats. Allow us to throw items from ammo slot and kep a stat item range slot or add bow equivalent items for throwing (throwing gloves, magical sharpening stones, etc.)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Abilities - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Curently being discussed additions to the item have been passed along&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The level 67 snare is random duration. All other snares are fixed duration.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Frenzy and Kick are on same timers, separate them.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We need a Stun and SNARE on different timers.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Stun Endurance cost needs to be lowered&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Snare should scale with each new rank (level 8 snare is as good at the level 65 one)&amp;nbsp; I suggest 1 minute, 2 minute, 3 minute set times on each.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Jolt needs its own timer as well…&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Endurance Regen -&lt;FONT color=#9933ff&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated, reworded and added information has been passed along&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Innate Endurance regen doesn't improve from 65 to 70 while all abilities become more costly in endurance cost.&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Berserkers suffer the most from endurance use, so there must be a way for us to get better endurance return… I suggest Flowing Thought for endurance&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;No Raid Utility - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated, reworded version has been passed along&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We need something besides medicore dps to help our group/raid.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Ideas tossed around are more combat abilities, innate group bonuses, AE Warcrys, and AE abilities that improve the raid. (Maybe + Accuracy or + Strikethrough).&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We should be able to provide such skills most of the time, NOT like current Warcry only once every 30 minutes.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;We need something class defining that gives us an attractive niche to fill.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improved DPS -&amp;nbsp;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt; - &lt;FONT size=2&gt;DPS for all classes to be&amp;nbsp;re-evaluated in the future&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;I have done much research into the damage comparisons of Rogues, Warriors, Monks, and Berserkers; I have found that Rogues do the most DPS by a large margin… Berserkers do about 60% of what a rogue can do.&amp;nbsp; That means that 1 rogue is worth 2 berserkers, since we have no other utility to offer outside of our DPS.&amp;nbsp; My suggestion is to somehow improve our DPS to at least 80% of a rogue&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;By limiting berserkers to 2handed weapons only, you have extremely limited our paths of progression.&amp;nbsp; The quality of 2handers coming out of GoD is also very bad…. They are either too fast, or have no AC.&amp;nbsp; You introduced a lot of 2handers with dumb procs like Guard 3… WHY!?&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/OL&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
